column5: seems you're right, but I enjoy his company so I can deal with just washing lures now and then  but you're welcome in my boat anytime Roy , just wear a nice shirt

spent 4 hours breaking her in...ran great  I saw something real interesting on the side scan  I zoomed in and put a waypoint went back over it and took a photo of the screen, it didn't show up real well, but next time out I will stop and check it out
I see mom and kiddie are doing fine.LOL
Sweet set up Terry! Great versitile fishing machine! Great job on the rigging!  S.

got the call at 11:25 my kicker motor is in quick run to the bank...need money to pay for it back home get the honda 5hp off and all the downrigger stuff and off I go to king city drop the boat off run over to BPS, couldn't find anything to spend my money on but killed an hour back to my boat and they are just finishing up.... back home with the complete package new 9.9 mec pro kicker \ now it's fishing time....
Good to hear Terry,now your complete !!!For now anyways.  .
Congrats!!! That looks NICE! I've lost track of the thread...is the kicker sharing fuel with the Optimax or is it on its own tank?
Lookin good Terry!
The 125 finally gave birth.   YA BABY BOOYA.  I think a good test this saturday,to get the ones you guys missed yesterday.
And,is it on it,s own battery?
Oh and is the speed control on too?  So many questions.  You would think it was mine.LMAO

right now it shares the same battery, that will change real soon shares gas from the onboard tank, but can use it's own tank if I want  oh and What do you do when you bring home a new motor you open it up and work on it  I just installed the troll master  speed control, easy job  http://s25.photobucket.com/user/Mrbeee1954/media/DSCF4540_zps5dc825fa.jpg.html" target="_blank">
Sweet.
I'd say!!
Based on reports of your reputation, you need some real anglers to get her slimed  Looks like a real nice boat.
I don't know if I can have it broken in by then
Wow, sweet rig man. The new kicker is shweeeeeeet!!!!
Yer on holidays. Do I need to take days off to do it for ya?
You have Thursday and Friday!  .lol.
10 hours of trolling at 1/2 to 3/4 rpm to break it in , I will have to troll for muskie  does simcoe have muskie ..lol
ok   lol
sweet set up. One windy day oughta use up the break in throttle requirements - or a good sized drift sock - heck you're gonna need at least one of those for fine motor control aren't ya?
i have one, so I just might use it
Nice!!
Sweet set up Terry.      Jealous!

Come on Terry... you know it's not complete! Now you need the second battery and the charging isolator that the dealer should have put in... more trolling spoons... more track accessories.. auto pilot...  A very nice riding boat... as I can say I have had the honour !  ...btw.. did you get the gas tank with the 9.9 ? They come into the dealer with tank and they usually grab them and throw them on the store shelf after hooking your motor up to the boat tank.
Looking good Terry!  Not you, the boat.
thanks all        yeah I am sure I will never be through buy stuff for it  and no tank came with it it was great getting out washing lures with you
If you want to catch fish you need to take me out there. Taking Wayne fishing is akin to having a bunch of bananas in your livewell.
